00:05:36.410 --> 00:05:40.170
First of all, one of the most
important points that I would make

00:05:40.170 --> 00:05:47.400
about Morocco and its history
is the inherent diversity

00:05:47.400 --> 00:05:49.150
in the country itself.

00:05:49.150 --> 00:05:52.430
How many of you have
been to Morocco?

00:05:52.430 --> 00:05:57.960
OK. So, you know, you know
what I'm talking about already.

00:05:57.960 --> 00:06:02.300
But for everybody to be on the
same page let us do a little bit

00:06:02.300 --> 00:06:06.260
of a background here that
the inherent diversity

00:06:06.260 --> 00:06:10.930
of Morocco is certainly one
of the most valuable elements

00:06:10.930 --> 00:06:17.580
of Moroccan society and perhaps
one of the most promising elements

00:06:17.580 --> 00:06:21.330
for humanity in general, if I
may wax a little bit polemical

00:06:21.330 --> 00:06:22.630
for a moment.

00:06:22.630 --> 00:06:26.570
But the diversity there in
terms of ethnic diversity,

00:06:26.570 --> 00:06:31.250
there are several languages
that are spoken in Morocco,

00:06:31.250 --> 00:06:38.070
the Amazigh dialect of the
popularly known Berber community,

00:06:38.070 --> 00:06:42.900 position:56%
which is the native North
Africans; there's Arabic, of course,

00:06:42.900 --> 00:06:49.000
and that being a Maghrebi or
North African dialect that Arabic:

00:06:49.000 --> 00:06:54.460
there's Hebrew; and, of course,
there's French and there's Spanish.

00:06:54.460 --> 00:06:59.280
So there's quite a lot of
linguistic diversity going

00:06:59.280 --> 00:07:01.220
on in Morocco itself.

00:07:01.220 --> 00:07:02.520
And, of course, with all

00:07:02.520 --> 00:07:07.480
of that linguistic diversity
comes also a diversity in religion

00:07:07.480 --> 00:07:11.120
and even in racial background.

00:07:11.120 --> 00:07:15.380
So as I mentioned before already
we have the North African Native

00:07:15.380 --> 00:07:19.140
community, but we have
the Arabic community

00:07:19.140 --> 00:07:21.910
which is the Arab communities
been there already for several,

00:07:21.910 --> 00:07:25.950
several centuries since the
early expansion of Islam

00:07:25.950 --> 00:07:28.280
across North Africa to the West.

00:07:28.280 --> 00:07:33.970
And then the Jewish community dates
back 2000 years, the destruction

00:07:33.970 --> 00:07:38.370
of the Second Temple
in Jerusalem, well,

00:07:38.370 --> 00:07:41.250
destruction of the First Temple
actually began the Jewish Diaspora

00:07:41.250 --> 00:07:45.600
as we know it, but by the Second
Temple certainly Jews are traveling

00:07:45.600 --> 00:07:51.310 position:56%
further afield and ending up in many
different parts of the Roman world

00:07:51.310 --> 00:07:55.960
and Morocco itself was
part of that constellation.

00:07:55.960 --> 00:07:59.510
So, that is really
very deeply inherent.

00:07:59.510 --> 00:08:06.220 position:56%
We also have the Sub-Saharan African
community, the Gnaoua community

00:08:06.220 --> 00:08:10.820
in Morocco brought across
the Saharan Arab slave trade

00:08:10.820 --> 00:08:18.290
and certainly infusing a large West
African presence in the county.

00:08:18.290 --> 00:08:22.800
What we'll get to, we'll get to
a little bit more in a moment.

00:08:22.800 --> 00:08:28.350
So, just a couple photos to
kind of represent this idea.

00:08:28.350 --> 00:08:34.970
This is a Quran, picture of
a Quran written in Morocco.

00:08:34.970 --> 00:08:43.420
This is a collection of Torah
scrolls in the Aron or the cabinet

00:08:43.420 --> 00:08:49.020
of a Moroccan synagogue and
they are uniquely Moroccan

00:08:49.020 --> 00:08:52.480
and that they are standing
up in these kind

00:08:52.480 --> 00:08:57.780
of very ornate round
encasings with scarves

00:08:57.780 --> 00:08:59.290
on them and things like that.

00:08:59.290 --> 00:09:01.630
And then we have here the Hamsa,

00:09:01.630 --> 00:09:08.390 position:56%
which is a very prominent symbol
throughout the Middle Eastern world.

00:09:08.390 --> 00:09:13.370
But, and if you notice, the
writing on it is actually Amazigh,

00:09:13.370 --> 00:09:15.250
which is the Berber dialect.

00:09:15.250 --> 00:09:20.110
So, we have this kind
of juxtaposition

00:09:20.110 --> 00:09:25.300
of this diversity just
everywhere in Moroccan society.

00:09:26.950 --> 00:09:29.230
Certainly, we must
also take into account

00:09:29.230 --> 00:09:32.030
that there's regional
diversity in Morocco.

00:09:32.030 --> 00:09:34.860
Certainly there are
villages and there are cities

00:09:34.860 --> 00:09:37.860
and there are coastal
areas and inland areas.

00:09:37.860 --> 00:09:46.520 position:56%
So, you know, that has an effect too
on the culture of Morocco overall.

00:09:46.520 --> 00:09:50.340
And topographically, too, we
have quite a diversity going on.

00:09:50.340 --> 00:09:54.560
We have several mountain ranges--
some of you have probably traveled

00:09:54.560 --> 00:09:59.010
through the Atlas perhaps even
the Rift Mountains in the north.

00:09:59.010 --> 00:10:00.850
