some really interesting pieces

00:23:29.730 --> 00:23:34.460
that combined, you know, this
diversity within the music

00:23:34.460 --> 00:23:35.840
that you can really hear.

00:23:35.840 --> 00:23:41.350
The melodic stuff I'm talking about
mixed with the language of Haketia

00:23:41.350 --> 00:23:44.220
which is the Judeo-Español dialect.

00:23:44.220 --> 00:23:52.230
So, in sum, what I'm getting
to is that Morocco's diversity,

00:23:52.230 --> 00:24:00.360
its inherent diversity in its
topography, in its ethnicity,

00:24:00.360 --> 00:24:08.320
in its languages, in its musical
styles is forming a soundscape,

00:24:08.320 --> 00:24:10.450
OK, a Moroccan soundscape.

